.SH NAME
EXT_sRGB \- EXT_sRGB extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]EXT_sRGB\f[B]\f[R] extension is part of the WebGL API and
adds sRGB support to textures and framebuffer objects.
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This extension is only available to WebGL1 contexts.
In WebGL2, the functionality of this extension is available on the
WebGL2 context by default.
The constants in WebGL2 are: \f[CR]gl.SRGB\f[R], \f[CR]gl.SRGB8\f[R],
\f[CR]gl.SRGB8_ALPHA8\f[R] and
\f[CR]gl.FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING\f[R].
.RE
.SH CONSTANTS
This extension exposes the following constants, which can be used in the
\f[CR]texImage2D()\f[R], \f[CR]texSubImage2D()\f[R],
\f[CR]renderbufferStorage()\f[R] and
\f[CR]getFramebufferAttachmentParameter()\f[R] methods.
.TP
\f[B]ext.SRGB_EXT\f[R]
Unsized sRGB format that leaves the precision up to the driver.
.TP
\f[B]ext.SRGB_ALPHA_EXT\f[R]
Unsized sRGB format with unsized alpha component.
.TP
\f[B]ext.SRGB8_ALPHA8_EXT\f[R]
Sized (8\-bit) sRGB and alpha formats.
.TP
\f[B]ext.FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING_EXT\f[R]
Returns the framebuffer color encoding (\f[CR]gl.LINEAR\f[R] or
\f[CR]ext.SRGB_EXT\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ext = gl.getExtension(\[dq]EXT_sRGB\[dq]);

\f[B]const\f[R] texture = gl.createTexture();
gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texture);

gl.texImage2D(
  gl.TEXTURE_2D,
  0,
  ext.SRGB_EXT,
  512,
  512,
  0,
  ext.SRGB_EXT,
  gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE,
  image,
);
.EE
